metadata.name: muy bn
metadata.description:
"muy bn" as in very good... Colloquially written. This is a "wena onda" (cool vibes) collage from street artworks from Bogotá and Cali, in Colombia.

I started with a Cartesian plane of 4 pictures and from there pasted a couple of stickers here, a couple of graffitis there... And suddenly this 7650x9900 noisy px image came up. And later a whole series both in color and BW.

From this one I would feature the mexican mariachi ad, the complot theories and the sticker that says "sos mi película" (you are my movie), which I find very deterministc. In general I love the mixture of political, commercial and artistic imprints in the walls which shows a great spectrum of feelings of a community. 

To find in the collage:
- A devil.
- A cigarrete with wings
- Different art disciplines
- How many cats are there?
- The meaning of the complot
